subject: p16055653
History: Line placement, to assess for pneumothorax.
Findings: In comparison with the study of, there has been placement of a right IJ catheter that extends to the lower portion of the SVC. No evidence of pneumothorax or widening of the mediastinum. In comparison with the prior study, there are even lower lung volumes, but otherwise little change in the appearance of the heart and lungs.
